genresAdvancedInfo.name: german blues
genresAdvancedInfo.description: German blues is a genre of music that combines elements of traditional blues music with German folk music. It is characterized by its melancholic, soulful sound, with slow, bluesy guitar riffs and emotive vocals. The lyrics often focus on themes of love, loss, and heartbreak, and are delivered in a heartfelt, expressive style.
